2026-04-20 19:09:27 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Ambient Sensor Module: Power Supply Decoupling/Bypass Capacitor (missing or faulty)'] hypothesis_explanation='The extensive testing has ruled out wiring, connections, sensor and relay faults, and correct polarity is confirmed. All measurements show expected voltages but persistent instability/oscillation across the entire ambient sensor module, affecting relay operation regardless of sensor state or direct relay actuation. The circuit simulation consistently fails to converge, which in real systems is often due to lack of supply decoupling or bypass capacitors in sensitive analog/digital modules. Missing or faulty capacitors would allow noise or oscillatory feedback between power, sensor, and relay circuits, causing repeated relay cycling and lamp instability as observed. The instability persists even with the sensor replaced by a resistor, implicating fundamental module power decoupling as the root cause.'
