description: Measure the DC voltage and check for AC ripple/noise directly across the battery terminals in the power supply module. A weak, low, or noisy supply could induce instability or oscillation in downstream modules, especially sensitive sensor circuits. This will help determine if the root cause is related to insufficient or unstable power supply., outcome='The measured voltage across the battery terminals is 12.0\u202fV (positive to negative). The simulation did not converge, indicating the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state. No polarity inversion is reported in the measured connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient Sensor Module (all input and output cable pairs simultaneously),
description: Simultaneously disconnect and test all four control cables (inputs and outputs) to the ambient sensor module at once. With no connections to external modules, measure continuity, resistance, and any possible unexpected shorts, especially across pairs or between input and output terminals. Inspect for accidental internal bridging, sneak paths, or unintentional module-to-module connections that could cause oscillation by forming feedback loops. Document results for each pair and between each pair., outcome='All four control cables show nominal continuity individually. There is a direct short between Control Input Cable (+) and Control Output Cable (+) (0.11 Ω), and between Control Input Cable (−) and Control Output Cable (−) (0.10 Ω). Continuity and resistance checks across other combinations yield resistive values (~1.2–1.4 Ω), and no accidental internal bridging or sneak paths were detected, but be aware that a simulation instability or oscillation was noted during one test. No polarity inversion was observed in the inspected connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=305.0, cost_breakdown=[('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 0.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Ambient Sensor Module Relay Coil,
description: Visually inspect the relay coil and its immediate wiring for signs of physical damage, improper soldering, broken leads, or manufacturing defects. Also check for signs of a miswired coil or unintended shunt path that could compromise relay isolation., outcome='No observable physical damage, broken leads, improper soldering, or internal faults were detected in the relay, cables, or inspection panel. All cables appear connected without visible internal defects. No polarity inversion was detected based on the inspection of cable labels and connection descriptions.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
